#: ../../N/nerd.rst:5
msgid "nerd"
msgstr "nerd"

#: ../../N/nerd.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../N/nerd.rst:10
msgid ""
"[mainstream slang] Pejorative applied to anyone with an above-average IQ and"
" few gifts at small talk and ordinary social rituals."
msgstr "[主流派の俗語] 平均以上のIQを持ち、雑談や普通の社交儀礼の才能に乏しい人に適用される蔑称。"

#: ../../N/nerd.rst:13
msgid ""
"[jargon] Term of praise applied (in conscious ironic reference to sense 1) "
"to someone who knows what's really important and interesting and doesn't "
"care to be distracted by trivial chatter and silly status games. Compare "
":ref:`geek`\\."
msgstr ""
"[ジャーゴン] "
"(語義1への意識的な皮肉として)本当に重要で面白いことを知っていて、些細なおしゃべりやくだらない地位ゲームに気を散らされたくない人に適用される称賛の語。\\"
" :ref:`geek`\\ と比較せよ。"

#: ../../N/nerd.rst:16
msgid ""
"The word itself appears to derive from the lines \"And then, just to show "
"them, I'll sail to Ka-Troo / And Bring Back an It-Kutch, a Preep and a Proo,"
" / A Nerkle, a Nerd, and a Seersucker, too!\" in the Dr. Seuss book *If I "
"Ran the Zoo* (1950). (The spellings ‘nurd’ and ‘gnurd’ also used to be "
"current at MIT, where ‘nurd’ is reported from as far back as 1957; however, "
":ref:`knurd` appears to have a separate etymology.) How it developed its "
"mainstream meaning is unclear, but sense 1 seems to have entered mass "
"culture in the early 1970s (there are reports that in the mid-1960s it meant"
" roughly \"annoying misfit\" without the connotation of intelligence."
msgstr ""
"この語自体は、Dr. Seussの本\\ *If I Ran the Zoo*\\ (1950)の「そしてやつらに見せてやるために、おれはKa-"
"Trooまで航海して/It-"
"KutchとPreepとProoを連れ帰ってやる、/NerkleとNerdとSeersuckerもな!」という行に由来するようだ。(綴り‘nurd’と‘gnurd’もかつてMITで使われていた。MITでは‘nurd’が1957年まで遡って報告されている。ただし\\"
" :ref:`knurd`\\ "
"は別の語源を持つようだ。)それがどう主流派の意味を発展させたかは不明だが、語義1は1970年代初頭に大衆文化に入ったようだ(1960年代半ばには知性の含意なしに、おおむね「うっとうしい不適合者」を意味していたという報告がある)。"

#: ../../N/nerd.rst:21
msgid ""
"Hackers developed sense 2 in self-defense perhaps ten years later, and some "
"actually wear \"Nerd Pride\" buttons, only half as a joke. At MIT one can "
"find not only buttons but (what else?) pocket protectors bearing the slogan "
"and the MIT seal."
msgstr ""
"ハッカーはおそらく10年ほど後に、自己防衛のために語義2を発展させ、一部は半ば冗談で実際に「Nerd "
"Pride」バッジを着けている。MITではバッジだけでなく、(他に何があろう?)そのスローガンとMITの紋章を冠したポケットプロテクタを見つけることができる。"
